## Dependencies

Common dependencies:

- Governance approval for execution-sensitive behavior.
- Security/compliance review before production claims.
- Treasury policy before any value movement.
- Current validation evidence before maturity promotion.
- AxodusAPP/Core consumer contract review where applicable.

Nucleus-specific dependencies are documented in each local `STATUS.md`.

## Production And Execution Policy

Global production status: DISABLED

Not authorized by this cycle:

- production readiness claims;
- real billing;
- payment execution;
- wallet signing;
- on-chain writes;
- token minting/transfers;
- treasury movement;
- trading execution;
- DEX swaps or liquidity routing;
- mining payouts;
- marketplace settlement;
- ACS autonomous execution;
- production exchange credentials.

## Validation Summary

Validation performed in this cycle:

- file existence checks for all created `STATUS.md` and maturity assessment files;
- markdown structure inspection;
- forbidden-claim scan across new/updated `.instructions` files;
- root Git check confirming `/opt/Axodus` is not a Git repository.

Product validation commands run where safe:

| Nucleus | Command | Result |
|---|---|---|
| Academy | `npm run typecheck && npm run lint && npm run test -- --run` | PASS; tests 1 file / 20 tests |
| ACS | `npm test` | PASS; build PASS and 152 tests PASS |
| Business | Not run | BLOCKED; `node_modules` missing and no install approved |
| Marketplace | `pnpm -r test` | PASS; 11 files / 102 tests |
| Mining | `pnpm test` | PASS_WITH_WARNINGS; 4 files / 47 tests, React Router/chart warnings |
| Trading | Not run | BLOCKED; no root `package.json`, nested E2E path requires dedicated request |

Product validation was not used to authorize production execution or to promote beyond the conservative L3 candidate baseline.

## Portfolio-Level Recommendation

The portfolio now has comparable baseline status files for the six previously undocumented nuclei. The next cycle should not resume DEX functional work. It should execute targeted validation-refresh requests in priority order:

1. Business dependency/validation baseline.
2. Mining validation and provider boundary review.
3. Academy validation and reward/contract boundary review.
4. Marketplace validation and payment/settlement boundary review.
5. ACS guarded execution validation under HOLD.
6. Trading credential and local E2E validation under HOLD.

Recommendation: PORTFOLIO_STATUS_NORMALIZED
